name: Sanctuary
directions: They don't always answer the doorbell but will when able to.
comment:
This is a faith-based outreach program focused on becoming a healthy, welcoming community in which people who are poor and excluded are particularly valued. This community is an expression of the good news embodied in Jesus Christ.
They don't have a specific gender-neutral bathroom, but their handicapped washroom is open for people who aren't comfortable in binary washrooms.

They also have a women's group on Mondays where transwomen are welcome.

name: Seton Hill Campus Lowe Hall
directions: When you enter the dining hall, you exit through the wooden door into the main building. Continue down the hallway and you will see an alcove where the gendered bathrooms are. Turn right and continue down the hall until you see a very large wooden door with a Family Restroom sign next to it. This is the gender neutral restroom.

name: Reeves Library Seton Hill Campus
directions: There are 3 in the building. One is in the bottom floor of the library, back hallway past the gendered bathrooms. If you enter from the top floor, take a left at the front doors, walk down the steps. Go through the doors to the study room. Go all the way to the back past all the bookshelves. Go through the door there. Go into the hallway and the gendered bathrooms will be on the left. Past those is 2 gender neutral single rooms. The other is on the main floor. If you enter through the top floor, continue into the library towards left and towards the back. You will see a water fountain. The gender neutral restroom is right next to it.
comment: You could ask the front desk when you first walk in for directions if you get lost. Most of the student who work there are friendly.
